# LLM Provider Abstraction

## Multi-provider mandatory

Klient może chcieć użyć dowolnego LLM providera. **Zero vendor lock-in**:

| Provider | Use case | Default model | SDK |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Anthropic** (primary) | Design generation, multi-variant orchestration | `claude-sonnet-4-6` | `@anthropic-ai/sdk` |
| **OpenAI** (alternative) | Klient z OpenAI subscription | `gpt-5` (or gpt-4.6) | `openai` |
| **Google Gemini** (alternative) | Klient z Google Workspace | `gemini-2.5-pro` | `@google/genai` |

## Provider interface

```typescript
// src/llm/types.ts
export interface LLMProvider {
  readonly name: string;
  readonly defaultModel: string;
  complete(messages: ChatMessage[], opts?: CompleteOptions): Promise<CompleteResult>;
  stream(messages: ChatMessage[], opts?: CompleteOptions): AsyncIterable<string>;
  countTokens(text: string): number;
}

export interface ChatMessage {
  role: "system" | "user" | "assistant";
  content: string;
}

export interface CompleteOptions {
  model?: string;
  temperature?: number;
  maxTokens?: number;
  responseFormat?: "text" | "json";
}

export interface CompleteResult {
  content: string;
  model: string;
  inputTokens: number;
  outputTokens: number;
  stopReason?: string;
}
```

## LLMRouter pattern

```typescript
// src/llm/router.ts
export class LLMRouter {
  private providers = new Map<string, LLMProvider>();
  private defaultKey: string | null = null;

  register(key: string, provider: LLMProvider): this {
    this.providers.set(key, provider);
    this.defaultKey ??= key;  // first registered = default
    return this;
  }

  setDefault(key: string): this { /* ... */ }
  pick(key?: string | null): LLMProvider { /* ... */ }
  list(): string[] { return [...this.providers.keys()]; }
  describe(): Array<{ key: string; name: string; defaultModel: string }> { /* ... */ }
  has(key: string): boolean { return this.providers.has(key); }
}
```

## Peer-dep design

✅ **SDK installation = opt-in**. LLMRouter NIE ma direct dep na żaden LLM SDK:

```typescript
// src/llm/providers/AnthropicProvider.ts
export interface AnthropicSdkLike {
  messages: {
    stream: (params: never) => never;  // typed loosely — caller wstrzykuje real SDK
  };
}

export interface AnthropicProviderConfig {
  sdk: AnthropicSdkLike;  // caller wstrzykuje initialized SDK instance
}

export class AnthropicProvider implements LLMProvider {
  // ... uses config.sdk dla calls
}
```

User installuje only SDK których chce używać:
```bash
pnpm add @anthropic-ai/sdk     # gdy chce Anthropic
pnpm add openai                # gdy chce OpenAI
pnpm add @google/genai         # gdy chce Gemini
```

## Initialization pattern

```typescript
// app startup
import { LLMRouter, AnthropicProvider, OpenAIProvider, GeminiProvider, MockProvider } from "@/llm";

const router = new LLMRouter();
router.register("mock", new MockProvider());  // zawsze available dla dev/CI

if (process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY) {
  const { default: Anthropic } = await import("@anthropic-ai/sdk");
  const sdk = new Anthropic({ apiKey: process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY });
  router.register("anthropic", new AnthropicProvider({ sdk }));
}

if (process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY) {
  const { default: OpenAI } = await import("openai");
  const sdk = new OpenAI({ apiKey: process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY });
  router.register("openai", new OpenAIProvider({ sdk }));
}

if (process.env.GOOGLE_API_KEY) {
  const mod = await import("@google/genai");
  const sdk = new mod.GoogleGenAI({ apiKey: process.env.GOOGLE_API_KEY });
  router.register("gemini", new GeminiProvider({ sdk }));
}
```

## Skill execution z LLMRouter

```typescript
// src/skills/runner.ts
export async function runSkill(
  skillName: string,
  input: SkillInput,
  ctx: SkillContext,  // ctx.llmRouter wstrzykuje wybranego providera
): Promise<SkillOutput> {
  const skill = await loadSkill(skillName);
  const provider = ctx.llmRouter.pick(skill.modelHint);  // skill może preferować provider

  const result = await provider.complete([
    { role: "system", content: skill.instructions },
    { role: "user", content: input.brief },
  ], {
    temperature: 0.7,
    responseFormat: "json",
  });

  return parseSkillOutput(result.content);
}
```

## MockProvider dla dev/CI

✅ **MockProvider** zawsze rejestrowana — agent może iterować bez API key:

```typescript
export class MockProvider implements LLMProvider {
  readonly name = "Mock";
  readonly defaultModel = "mock-1";

  async complete(messages: ChatMessage[]): Promise<CompleteResult> {
    const userMsg = messages.find(m => m.role === "user");
    return {
      content: `[Mock] Response to: ${userMsg?.content.slice(0, 100)}`,
      model: "mock-1",
      inputTokens: 100,
      outputTokens: 50,
    };
  }

  async *stream(messages: ChatMessage[]) {
    yield "[Mock] ";
    yield "streaming ";
    yield "response.";
  }

  countTokens(text: string): number {
    return Math.ceil(text.length / 4);  // rough heuristic
  }
}
```

## Anti-patterns

❌ **Hardcoded SDK calls** w skill code:
```typescript
// ZŁY KOD
import Anthropic from "@anthropic-ai/sdk";
const client = new Anthropic({ apiKey: process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY });
const response = await client.messages.create({ ... });  // ZŁY — vendor lock-in
```

❌ **Provider check w skill**:
```typescript
// ZŁY KOD
if (process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY) {
  // call OpenAI
} else {
  // call Anthropic
}
```

❌ **No fallback gdy SDK missing** — runtime crash. Use graceful warn + Mock fallback.

❌ **Sync API calls** — wszystkie LLM operacje są async.

## Patterns

✅ **Provider-agnostic skill**:
```typescript
export async function generateHero(brief: string, ctx: SkillContext): Promise<HeroOutput> {
  const provider = ctx.llmRouter.pick();  // user picks default
  const result = await provider.complete([
    { role: "system", content: heroInstructions },
    { role: "user", content: brief },
  ]);
  return parseHero(result.content);
}
```

✅ **JSON-mode response gdy supported**:
```typescript
const result = await provider.complete(messages, {
  responseFormat: "json",  // provider opcjonalnie supports — fallback do parsing JSON z text
});
```

✅ **Token tracking dla cost monitoring**:
```typescript
ctx.logger.info(`Skill ${skillName}: ${result.inputTokens} in / ${result.outputTokens} out tokens`);
```

